{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Pay a \u00a32,500 bonus to all NHS employees.",
        "additional_details": "All NHS staff have been working all though the pandemic and put themselves at enormous risk by exposure to the disease, I would like to suggest that the Government pay a one-off bonus to all NHS staff to the same value as the monthly Furlough payments of \u00a32.5k\r\n\r\nThis would demonstrate to the NHS the high regard we all hold them in and give some appreciation to them for their efforts in the last year.",
        "background": "The Government have paid Furlough payments of up to \u00a32.5k a month per person to sustain people though the pandemic for over a year.\r\n\r\nThe Government have just announced a pay rise of 1% to NHS staff which barely covers inflation.\r\n\r\nPlease pay each of them a similar amount as a bonus",
